<!-- PJG ITAG l=71 g=1 f=3 -->
III. Program Participation Agreement 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=3 -->
A. Section 487(a)(5) requires an institution to provide 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
assurances that the institution will provide, upon request and in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a timely fashion, information relating to its administrative 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
capability and financial responsibility to the Secretary, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
designated State postsecondary review entity designated under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
subpart 1 of part H of Title IV of the HEA, the appropriate 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
guaranty agency, and accrediting agency or association. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Issues that the community was asked to address and the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
community's views: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1. How should agencies obtain this information from 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institutions? 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Other agencies should obtain the information through 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
IPEDS or accrediting agency annual reports. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
[San Francisco] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Requests should be made in writing to the Chief 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Executive Officer and the Chief Financial Officer of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the institution. [Kansas City] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
2. Should there be a standard information-sharing format? 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;There should be a standard information sharing format 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
provided that the institution is allowed to report 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
using its accounting system. [Kansas City] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;There needs to be a standard information sharing format 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that can be completed readily and corresponds to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institution's fiscal year. [New York] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The Department should provide a single form that can be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
used for all agencies. [Atlanta] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
B. Section 487(a)(8)(B) requires institutions that advertise job 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
placement rates to make available to prospective students 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
relevant State licensing requirements for any job for which the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
course of instruction is designed to prepare the student. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Issues that the community was asked to address and the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
community's views: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1. How often should institutions be required to update 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
licensing data? 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Institutions should update the data whenever State 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
licensing agencies require that updates or regulation 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
must occur. [San Francisco, Kansas City, Atlanta] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Information always needs to be current. [New York] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
2. Should there be a standard format for providing this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
information to prospective students? 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;A typical brochure should be used to convey information 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to students. [San Francisco] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;There should not be a standard format for providing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
this information to prospective students. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
[Kansas City, New York, Atlanta] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The institution should use the States required format 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for providing consumer data to students. If the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Secretary requires additional information, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
information should be consistent with the formats that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the institution already uses. [Kansas City] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
C. Section 487(a)(13) provides that an institution may not deny 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal financial aid to an eligible student because the student 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
is studying abroad in a program approved for credit by the home 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institution. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Issues that the community was asked to address and the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
community's views: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1. Should a consortium agreement be required? 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;A consortium agreement should not be required. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
[Kansas City, San Francisco] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;A consortium agreement should be used for pre-approved 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
work. Institutions need to ensure that two 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institutions are not giving aid at the same time. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
[New York] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;A consortium agreement should be required if the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
student is paying tuition at the home institution and a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
second institution is involved. Otherwise no consortium agreement should be required. [Atlanta] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
2. Does the study-abroad program have to be part of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
student's program at the home institution? 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The study abroad program need not be a part of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
student's program at the home institution, but must 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
count toward a degree at the institution. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
[Kansas City] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The study abroad program should be a part of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
student's home program. [San Francisco, Atlanta] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



