<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=1 -->
4. Should the Secretary compile and maintain a list of State 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
tuition recovery funds if that meets the requirements that permit 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
an institution's participation in that fund to operate in lieu of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
its cash reserve requirements? 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The Secretary should compile and maintain a list of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
State tuition recovery funds that meet the requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that permit an institution's participation in that fund 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to operate in lieu of the cash reserve requirements. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
[New York, San Francisco, Atlanta] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;An institution should provide the name and address of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the State tuition recovery fund to confirm that they 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
will be able to use the State tuition recovery fund to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
pay refunds. [Atlanta] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
G. Section 498(d) authorizes the Secretary to establish 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
procedures and standards relating to administrative capability, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
including the consideration of past performance of institutions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or individuals in control of such institutions and maintenance of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
records. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=21 g=1 f=3 -->
Issues that the community was asked to address and the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
community's views: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1. What measures of past performance will be used, and what 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
time periods should be included in the review? 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;No other standards of administrative capability or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
financial responsibility should be considered. There 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
is an inundation of oversight responsibility and the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements placed on institutions is sufficient. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
[Kansas City, San Francisco, Atlanta] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;In certain cases, institutional administrators should 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
meet a minimum experience requirement (e.g., five years 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of prior experience in administration.) [San Francisco] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;School owners, corporate directors and officers, and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the chief school administrator should be required to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
monitor and investigate school compliance, take 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
whatever steps are within the person's authority to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
effect the correction of non-compliance, and report to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Department, the accrediting agency, and the State 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
licensing agency any non-compliance that has not been 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
corrected. California law requires this. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
[San Francisco] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The current &sect;668.14 and &sect;668.15 should be used to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
measure administrative capability with the exception of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the withdrawal rates. [Kansas City] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;A minority of the group recommended that the Secretary 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
look into all complaints filed against institutions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with the local law enforcement authorities even though 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the complaint may not warrant pulling of an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institution's license or loss of accreditation. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
[Kansas City] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The Department should look at the past two audits to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
see that performance reviews have corrected all the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
deficiencies as a basis that the institution is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
administratively capable. This should not be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determined arbitrarily, but should be determined by a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
review. [New York] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Research data is needed to establish a basis for past 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
performance. Other measures of past performance that 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
should be used: Placement, default and withdrawal 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rates, past performance reviews and implementation of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
recommendations, personnel turnover, and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
faculty/student ratio. [San Francisco] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Default rates, course completion and withdrawal rates, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and job placement rates must be considered together. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
These should be triggers that, in certain combinations, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
should cause more review of administrative capability. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Mitigating circumstances must be considered. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
[New York] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Standards for default rates, course completion and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
withdrawal rates, and job placement rates should be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
applicable to all institutions. No new standards 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
should be set without historical data. [San Francisco] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;Student or consumer complaints against an institution 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
should be taken into consideration if a pattern of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
legitimate complaints indicate a need for review by an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
outside entity. [New York] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;There should be no standard measure of an institution's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
administrative capability with respect to student or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consumer complaints against an institution. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Department should review trends and the nature of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
complaints. [San Francisco] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
H. Section 498(g) provides that the Secretary may certify an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
institution's eligibility for a period not to exceed four years. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Issues that the community was asked to address and the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
community's views: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
1. Should the Secretary adopt rules addressing the length of a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
period of eligibility and if so what should these standards be? 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The four-year periods of eligibility should be based on 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
award years. [Kansas City] 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
